o.d: Located close to New Delhi Railway Station, it is an old and busy area. Find cheap travel accommodation here. Explore the congested market lanes for buying trendy accessories.
Located close to the city’s airport, Mahipalpur is a commercial area packed with pocket-friendly hotels and multi-cuisine restaurants.
A blend of the commercial and residential arena. Gaffar Market and Ajmal Khan Road are famous markets. Hunt the crowded streets for garment and electronic shopping.
An upscale residential area. Dine at stylish cafes, shop for fashionable apparel, footwear and accessories at the local market and designer stores.
Entertainment hub and commercial centre of the city. Find luxury hotels, corporate offices and consulates here. Shop at branded showrooms and dine at stylish restaurants and bars.
An upmarket area housing the picturesque Hauz Khas Fort and Deer Park. Enjoy vibrant nightlife at cafes and pubs in Hauz Khas Village. Drop at boutique stores for retail therapy.
Close to Delhi’s International Airport, Aerocity is a leisure destination with luxury hotels. Experience a great nightlife scene at lively bars, nightclubs and cafes.
An upmarket area housing the picturesque Hauz Khas Fort and Deer Park. Enjoy vibrant nightlife at cafes and pubs in Hauz Khas Village. Shop at famous boutique stores nearby.
Busy area housing the Humayun’s Tomb and Nizamuddin Railway Station. Eat at local restaurants serving delicious non-veg dishes and visit Hazrat Nizamuddin Auliya Dargah nearby.
Right in the heart of Old Delhi, it is a popular shopping hub. Walk down the narrow, crowded bylanes to shop for traditional apparel, jewellery, and spices.
